                    p(lang='en', dir='ltr')
                      | Dystopian future or 
                      a(href='https://twitter.com/hashtag/canyonfire2?src=hash&ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw') #canyonfire2
                      |  from 
                      a(href='https://twitter.com/Disneyland?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw') @Disneyland
                      a(href='https://twitter.com/hashtag/spacemountain?src=hash&ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw') #spacemountain
                      a(href='https://t.co/hydwnbqe3w') pic.twitter.com/hydwnbqe3w
                    | — Laura Olden (@LOldenPhoto) 
                    a(href='https://twitter.com/LOldenPhoto/status/917496226576084992?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw') October 9, 2017
                p California has been plagued with wildfires for the past 3 days. Over 100 people are in hospitals for burns varying in severity and smoke inhalation. Thirteen people were left dead. Another 20,000 were displaced due to forced evacuations and are still being left homeless, many stuck in makeshift shelters. 
                p The 17 separate wildfires are spread across northern California, occupying an area that spans around 3,250 square miles. Most of the fires are concentrated in areas north of Santa Rosa, the east side of Sugarloft Ridge State Park, and north of Napa. There is also a smaller wildfire between Sonoma and Napa.
                blockquote.twitter-tweet.tw-align-center(data-lang='en')
                  p(lang='en', dir='ltr')
                    | View from my sisters home right now. Praying this fire does not jump to their track 
